menu "breadboard: bb_log"

config BB_LOG_ROUTES
    bool "Build bb_log HTTP routes (log-level GET/POST)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_log compiles the routes module that exposes
        GET /api/log/level and POST /api/log/level. Adds bb_http, bb_json,
        and bb_registry to bb_log's PRIV_REQUIRES. Disable for headless
        logging-only consumers.

        The structured log stream is served separately via bb_event at
        GET /api/events?topic=log (see BB_LOG_EVENT_AUTO_ATTACH).

config BB_LOG_SSE_KEEPALIVE_MS
    int "SSE keepalive interval (ms)"
    default 5000
    range 1000 60000
    depends on BB_LOG_ROUTES
    help
        Vestigial — the /api/logs SSE route has been retired. This symbol
        is kept to avoid build breakage on boards that still reference it
        via sdkconfig. It is unused.

config BB_LOG_STREAM_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-init bb_log_stream via bb_registry early tier"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_log_stream_init is automatically invoked by
        bb_registry_init_early() without explicit app_main call.
        Disable to manually call bb_log_stream_init(). Independent of
        CONFIG_BB_LOG_ROUTES (stream capture vs. HTTP routes).

config BB_LOG_STREAM_BUF_BYTES
    int "Stream ringbuffer size (bytes)"
    default 6144
    range 512 65536
    help
        Size of the ringbuffer used to capture log lines for SSE consumers.
        Allocated on heap (SPIRAM-preferred with fallback) only when
        bb_log_stream_init() is called. Default 6144 bytes (6 KB).

config BB_LOG_UDP_SINK
    bool "Mirror log lines to a UDP datagram sink"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, bb_log compiles an optional UDP mirror output. A consumer
        calls bb_log_udp_enable(ip_be, port) at runtime to broadcast every
        formatted log line as a UDP datagram (one per line); a dedicated
        low-priority task owns the socket so sendto never runs inside the IDF
        log mutex. Intended for headless / pre-httpd states (e.g. OTA-only boot
        mode) where the SSE HTTP stream isn't reachable. Default off — the
        machinery is compiled out entirely. NOTE: log lines may carry SSID /
        hostname; enable deliberately.

config BB_LOG_TAG_REGISTRY_MAX
    int "Maximum number of log tag registry entries"
    default 24
    range 8 128
    help
        Maximum number of distinct log tags that can be registered via
        bb_log_tag_register(). Each entry is ~33 bytes BSS. Default 24
        covers typical firmware usage (14-16 tags) with comfortable headroom
        and saves 320 B BSS vs the old hardcoded value of 32. Raise if
        your application registers more than 24 distinct log tags.

config BB_LOG_STREAM_WRITER_QUEUE_LEN
    int "bb_log_stream writer queue depth"
    default 16
    range 4 64
    help
        Number of slots in the bb_log_stream writer queue. Each slot holds
        a log message (~200 B), so this directly sizes internal heap. Lower
        it (e.g. 8) on heap-tight no-PSRAM boards to reclaim ~1.6 KB at the
        cost of dropping log lines under burst logging. Default 16 keeps
        current behavior.

config BB_LOG_WRITER_TASK_STACK
    int "bb_log console-writer task stack size (bytes)"
    default 2048
    help
        Stack (bytes) for the bb_log_stream console-writer task (bb_log_writer),
        which drains the log queue to stdout. 2048 is sufficient for the
        non-blocking fwrite/fflush path; raise only if a consumer's logging
        path needs more. (B1-304)

config BB_LOG_EVENT_AUTO_ATTACH
    bool "Auto-attach 'log' bb_event stream topic to /api/events"
    default y
    depends on BB_EVENT_ROUTES_AUTOREGISTER
    help
        When enabled (default), bb_log registers a non-retained "log" bb_event
        stream topic and attaches it to /api/events at regular-tier order 4.
        This is THE primary log transport — structured JSON served at
        GET /api/events?topic=log; the legacy /api/logs raw-text SSE route
        has been retired.

        Each log line is forwarded as structured JSON:
        {"ts":<ms>,"level":"I|W|E|D|V|?","tag":"<tag>","msg":"<text>"}

        The forwarder feeds from a dedicated queue (see BB_LOG_EVENT_QUEUE_LEN)
        inside s_log_vprintf so the hot logging path is never blocked.

        Disable only if you want the log topic available to direct bb_event
        subscribers without surfacing it on /api/events.

config BB_LOG_EVENT_QUEUE_LEN
    int "Log event forwarder queue depth"
    default 48 if SPIRAM
    default 24
    range 8 256
    depends on BB_LOG_EVENT_AUTO_ATTACH
    help
        Number of slots in the off-hot-path forwarder queue between
        s_log_vprintf and the bb_log_event forwarder task. Each slot holds
        one log line (~192 B), so 48 slots ≈ ~9 KB worst-case buffering.
        Lines are dropped (with a counter) when the queue is full; the
        dropped count is visible via bb_log_event_dropped().

        PSRAM-axis DERIVE: default 48 on SPIRAM boards (ample heap); 24 on
        no-PSRAM boards (~4.6 KB, lower than the prior 48-slot default that
        allocated ~9 KB on heap-tight boards). Per-board sdkconfig fragments
        (e.g. esp32-s2-mini at 8) override this derive and take precedence.

endmenu
